 her activities and impact.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCountesseszEnglandvBiography. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 4aShakespeare 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aArbella Stuart.  aBess of Hardwick.  adomesticity.  aembroidery.  alanguage choice.  amarriage.  asuccession.1 aBryson, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrench, Sara L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrye, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHopkins, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHopkins, Lisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMalay, Jessica L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcus, Imogen Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaxwell, Felicity Lyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteen, Sara Jayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiggins, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610130340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526101303423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526101303/original  a978-3-11-128249-7  Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles